name: Cube loop #2
description: The Geometric shapes were created using Deneba Ultrapaint (1990) on a Macintosh Plus, and then imported into Deluxe Paint IV (1991) for the Amiga. These cubes are also used in designs for Kristen's weavings, and incorporate Taqueté weaving structures. This speaks to the history of computers, and weavings created from Jacquard/punched card looms being the first "digital" images created from stored data.
